    "statementHTML": "<div class=\"statement-body\">\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-goal\">\n   <h2><span class=\"icon icon-goal\">&nbsp;</span><span>Goal </span></h2>\n   <span class=\"question-statement\">Scientific notation generally assumes base 10, but it can be used with any base.<br><br>An <strong>e</strong> is used to imply 'exponent' where in base 10 this means <strong>*10^</strong> (<strong>times 10 to the power of</strong>), e.g. <const>2e4</const> = 2*10^4 = 20000.<br><br>Here we use a <strong>k</strong> to mean <strong>*1000^</strong> (<strong>times 1000 to the power of</strong>). Some examples are shown below, showing a number, then showing it represented in base 10 (<strong>e</strong>) and base 1000 (<strong>l</strong>) scientific notation.<br><br><const>1000000000000</const><br><strong>e</strong>: <const>1e12</const><br><strong>k</strong>: <const>1k4</const><br><br><const>2419300000000</const><br><strong>e</strong>: <const>2.4193e12</const><br><strong>k</strong>: <const>2.4193k4</const><br><br><const>400</const><br><strong>e</strong>: <const>4e2</const><br><strong>k</strong>: <const>400k0</const></span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-protocol\">\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-input\"><strong>1 line :</strong> an integer <var>n</var> for the number to represent in base 1 thousand scientific notation (NOTE: input as a string since some languages can't input integers larger than 2^31, HINT: you don't need big integer arithmetic to solve this)</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-output\"><strong>1 line :</strong> the number in base 1 thousand scientific notation formatted like <strong>[value]k[exponent]</strong></div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Constraints</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-constraints\">0 &lt; <var>n</var> &